Day 50 of Road to Fluent Spanish focused on final review and reinforcement of the weekly Puerto Rico conversational phrases, continued Pimsleur Unit 2 review, and additional travel, invitation, and communication vocabulary.

Duolingo review today included:
- El hotel está a cinco cuadras = The hotel is five blocks away
- ¿Cuántos invitados hay? = How many guests are there?
- La comida está lista = The food is ready
- Llegaremos muy pronto = We will arrive very soon
- Tu barrio = Your neighborhood
- Sí, en serio = Yes, seriously
- Ahora mismo = Right now
- Normalmente = Normally

Memrise review included:
- Checar = To check
- Dale clic en enviar = Click on send
- Prende = Turn on
- Prende la cámara = Turn on the camera
- Confirmado de recibido = Confirmation received
- El archivo = The file
- Mandar = To send
- Responde a este correo = Reply to this email

Completed the final day of this week’s Puerto Rico conversational phrase set:
- ¿Qué haces para divertirte aquí? = What do you do for fun here?
- ¿Qué playa me recomiendas? = What beach do you recommend?
- ¿Está lejos de aquí? = Is it far from here?
- ¿Cómo llego al Viejo San Juan? = How do I get to Old San Juan?
- ¿Qué lugares debería visitar? = What places should I visit?
- Quiero probar comida local = I want to try local food
- ¿Qué bebida me recomiendas? = What drink do you recommend?
- Hace mucho calor hoy = It’s very hot today
- Necesito practicar más español = I need to practice more Spanish
- Estoy disfrutando mucho Puerto Rico = I’m enjoying Puerto Rico a lot

Continued heavy review of Pimsleur Unit 2 Lesson 6 with focus on invitation phrasing, future tense, and conversational travel vocabulary:
- Tengo que irme la semana entrante = I have to leave next week
- Llegué ayer en la mañana = I arrived yesterday morning
- No puedo ir la semana entrante = I can’t go next week
- Me gustaría quedarme más tiempo = I’d like to stay longer
- ¿Vas a quedarte? = Are you going to stay?
- ¿Te gustaría venir mañana? = Would you like to come tomorrow?
- A veces tengo que viajar = Sometimes I have to travel
- ¿Cuánto tiempo vas a quedarte? = How long are you going to stay?
- Te invito a mi casa = I invite you to my house
- Nos invitan = They invite us
- Los invitamos = We invite them
- Tienes que venir = You have to come
- Hasta mañana = Until tomorrow
